The promotion rule:
  field name ends with `_id`:
    stem = strip `_id`
    target = snake_to_pascal(stem)
    if target in known_tables:
      Record(target)        -> TYPE record<target>
    else:
      Int                   -> TYPE int   (C12 fallback)
  else:
    Any                     -> TYPE any   (C12 default)

Real-world e2e through rails_mini fixture (filesystem-driven):
  TimeEntry has work_package_id -> WorkPackage is in the fixture's
  app/models/ -> emitted as option<record<WorkPackage>>.
  WorkPackage has status_id -> Status is NOT in the fixture -> stays
  option<int>. Asymmetric promotion demonstrates the join correctly.

